'''Christine Jacoba Aaftink''' (born 25 August 1966) is a retired [[Speed skating|speed skater]] from the Netherlands.<ref>[http://www.metronieuws.nl/sport/2009/01/ik-ben-in-verwachting-van-een-tweeling "I'm expecting twins"] ''Metro''. Retrieved 2015-08-22.</ref> She specialized in the 500 m and 1000 m distances, in which she competed at the 1988, 1992 and 1994 Winter Olympics. Her best achievements were fifth and fourth place in 1992 in 500 m and 1000 m, respectively.<ref name=r1>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/aa/christine-aaftink-1.html Christine Aaftink]. sports-reference.com</ref> In 1994 she was the [[List of flag bearers for the Netherlands at the Olympics|Olympic flag bearers for the Netherlands]]. She won two bronze medals at the [[World Sprint Speed Skating Championships for Women]] in 1990 and 1991.<ref name=r2>[http://www.schaatsstatistieken.nl/index.php?file=schaatser&code=1966082501 Christine Aaftink (NED)]. schaatsstatistieken.nl</ref>

Nationally, she won at least one [[KNSB Dutch Sprint Championships|sprint title]] every year between 1987 and 1996. She won all three (500 m, 1000 m and allround sprint) in 1990 and 1992–1994.<ref name=r2/>

Personal bests:<ref name=r1/> 
*500 m – 39.88 (1996)
*1000 m – 1:20.21 (1996)
*1500 m – 2:11.57 (1994)
* 3000 m – 5:04.33 (1987)

