The '''Jura Museum''' located in [[Willibaldsburg]] castle in the town of [[Eichstätt]], [[Germany]] is a Natural History Museum that has an extensive exhibit of [[Jurassic]] fossils from the quarries of [[Solnhofen]] and surroundings, including marine reptiles, [[pterosaur]]s, and one specimen of the early bird ''[[Archaeopteryx]]''.  The latest acquisition of the museum is the well preserved skeleton of the coelurosaur ''[[Juravenator]]''. 
The museum also has an aquarium, with several large tanks showing tropical fish and corals, as well as ''[[Nautilus]]''.

